The econometric methods covered in Economics 2222A/B and Economics 2223A/B are extended to common machine learning methods such as random forest and artificial neural networks.
Antirequisite(s): Data Science 3000A/B, the former Computer Science 4414A/B, the former Statistical Sciences 3850B, and the former Software Engineering 4460A.
Extra Information: 1 lecture hour, 2 laboratory hours.
